The distribution, history and current situation of adult education are discussed. Connections are made between adult developmental psychology and teaching. Various teaching methods are practiced.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop student competencies necessary for competent action in adult education and supporting the adult learner.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) describes the basic principles and forms of adult education; 2) can support an adult learner in overcoming learning barriers; 3) plans the training process considering the principle of constructive coherence; 4) applies different methods of teaching adults in his activities and in supporting self-development; 5) knows the various roles of the trainer and is ready to develop the necessary expertise to fulfill them; 6) values colleagues, learners, himself and other parties as an adult learner and supports his own and others' learning.
